WhoIsBot - Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 2024.01.22

This Privacy Policy explains how WhoIsBot ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use the WhoIsBot Discord bot (the "Bot"). By using the Bot, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect:

1.1. User-Provided Information: The Bot may collect information that you provide when using specific commands, such as the "/whois" command. This may include domain names or other information required for the functionality of the Bot.

1.2. Automatically Collected Information: The Bot may automatically collect technical information, such as server logs and usage data, to ensure proper functioning and improve user experience.

2. How We Use Your Information:

2.1. Providing Bot Services: We use the collected information to provide the functionality of the Bot, including processing commands and delivering requested information.

2.2. Improving Bot Performance: Collected data may be used to analyze and enhance the performance, features, and overall user experience of the Bot.

3. Data Sharing:

3.1. Third-Party Services: The Bot may use third-party services to retrieve information, such as domain details in response to the "/whois" command. These services have their own privacy policies, and you should review them for additional information.

4. Data Security:

4.1. We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

5. Your Choices:

5.1. You have the choice not to provide certain information, but this may limit your ability to use specific features of the Bot.

6. Changes to Privacy Policy:

6.1. We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. The latest version will be indicated by the "Last Updated" date. Continued use of the Bot after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

7. Contact Information:

7.1. For questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact WhoIsBot through Discord.

Thank you for using WhoIsBot!

